displayName.text: iPark - NYC Parking 555 West Garage Corporation

formattedAddress: 546 W 24th St, New York, NY 10011, USA
adrFormatAddress: 546 W 24th St, New York, NY 10011, USA

originalText.text: The parking attendant yelled at the man parking a car in front of me and also tried to pick a fight with me after finishing with him. He also charged me an extra 15$ on top of my spot hero reservation citing an oversize fee which was already included in the spot hero charge. I could not get my car without paying the fee. When I looked at the receipt after leaving, the fee was charged for overstaying my reservation, even though I left 30 min before it ended.

originalText.text:
This place deserves a zero star.
Staff here are very rude,   Always respond with nasty attitude even though I talk to them in a civil manner.  I asked for a receipt and the guy yelled at me saying that he can’t give me a “fake receipt” because I paid through an app. I told him not to worry about it but he kept coming at me. Unnecessary.
After I got in my car, just getting settled and plugging my phone(not even more than a minute). The guy came from behind with another customers car and beeped at me.

originalText.text: When I came to pick up my car at 11pm, there was a car running in front of the office (like it had just been dropped off), the office lights were on, but there was no one around. I waited about 10-15 minutes before I started calling out for an attendant to no avail. I looked all over the facility to see if anyone was there. I finally called the number on the ticket, the facility phone rang, and an attendant slowly and lazily got out of a car where he had been asleep. He made no apologies. Before I even got into my car, he had returned to the car he had gotten out of. The car with the engine running in front of the office remained in place with the engine running.

originalText.text:
Attendants were extremely rude & unprofessional (in total agreement with other reviews). While trying to explain that my car didn’t have an ignition (just to be thorough), he rolled his eyes, sighed, & raised his voice at me, “Don’t you see the sign?!” while pointing to the sign that said leave keys in ignition & roll the window down.

I forgot something in the trunk. Before he parked the car, I asked if he minded waiting a second while I retrieved item, again, he rolled his eyes & didn’t even respond, he just stopped the car & I got my item.

Also, I have a mid-sized SUV (which is practically the size of a normal car), & they insisted on charging $10 more than quoted price.

I have never had such horrible service at a parking garage in NYC. I would never even take the time to write a negative review unless I was truly taken aback.

Never coming back here again!

originalText.text: DO NOT PARK HERE. I always request a quote before leaving my car and always give very accurate times about when I am will be back. I park in Manhattan at various lots approx. 3 times a week and have never had this issue. When I returned I was asked for $20 more than the quote and offered absolutely no customer service about it, I was told to call the cops if I didn't like it then ignored while they helped three other people. When I called the next day to try and speak to a higher up I was given a hard time and just told, "we can't control it it's the computer", which is fine, just give a real quote then! I also specifically asked to not have my windows rolled down as they stick sometimes and when I came back all windows were down. AVOID, would give zero stars if possible.
